	<p>The cold season is a particularly dangerous time for stray dogs: they are hungry, and doghunters scatter poisoned food. The most common remedy is isoniazid. This drug is not harmful to humans, because freely sold in pharmacies. However, in certain doses, it is lethal for dogs. Including pets, because they walk in the same place as homeless people!</p>
